Citation.sTitle: Phase equilibrium for the systems diisopropyl ether, isopropyl alcohol + 2,2,4-trimethylpentane and + n-heptane at 101.3 kPa
Citation.sAbstract: Consistent vapour-liquid equilibrium data for the ternary systems diisopropyl ether + isopropyl alcohol  + 2,2,4-trimethylpentane and diisopropyl ether + isopropyl alcohol + n-heptane are reported at  101.3 kPa. The vapour liquid equilibrium data have been correlated by Wilson, NRTL and UNIQUAC  equations. The ternary systems do not present ternary azeotropes.
